  <h1>Node JS</h1>
  <p>
    Node JS is a javascript framework used to build server-side applications. Node JS can be used for frontend and backend aswell. 
  </p>

  <p>To get started with a node project, enter following command in your CLI in your repository:</p>
  <pre>
    <code>
      npm install node
    </code>
  </pre>
  <p>After the installation, a folder called 'node_modules' will apear in your repository. This folder isn't ment to be pushed or anything.<br>
  The package.json folder is where you'll find your dependencies, Scripts, application information and more.

  <p>This webpage uses multiplte packages, for example express, ejs and nodemon <br>
  The install commands for this has beeen:
  <pre>
      npm install express
      npm install nodemon
      npm install ejs
  </pre>
  
    <h2>Express</h2>
    
    <p>
      Express is a Node web framework.
      Express is used to make and create API's. <br>
      This is an example on how to setup a basic express server. 
    </p>
    <pre>
        const express = require('express')
        const app = express()
    </pre>
    <p>
    With express we are able to set some specific options for our project like: <br>
    - Set the location of the files there is rendered in this project <br>
    - setting up a live server on a port where the project is running
    </p>
    

