    <h2>Middleware functions</h2>
    <p>
      Middleware functions in node is functions that has  all the access for requesting an object and responding to an object.</p>
      <pre>
        function checkAuthenticated(req, res, next) {
          if (req.isAuthenticated()) {
            return next()
          }
          res.redirect('/login')
        }
      </pre>
      <p>
      Next is a Callback argument to the middleware function, called "next" by convention.
    </p>
